<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Melanospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanospora lagenaria" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="lagenaria">Melanospora lagenaria</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. caprina" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="caprina">M. caprina</taxonomicName>
, but the former has less tomentose ascomata with shorter necks ending in a poorly developed crown of setae. This species is also similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. arenaria" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="arenaria">M. arenaria</taxonomicName>
. For morphological comparison see Notes of the latter species.
</paragraph>
